condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, Article C.4 | Description :Upon completion of the dispersion modeling studies, theBorrower shall update and submit to the Bank, for its review, the ESIA and shall publicly disclose the revised ESIA as approved bythe Bank.

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section V, Article 1 | Description :Ratio of total operating revenues to total operating expenses ofnot less than 0.83 for fiscal year ending December 31, 2010; 0.86 for 2011; 0.88 for 2012; 0.91 for 2013 and 0.96 for 2014 and eachfiscal year thereafter occurring during the period of implementation, to be reported each year in respect of such year and thefollowing (forecast), as well as the previous year (actual). | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section V, Article 1 | Description :Ratio of total operating revenues to total operating expenses ofnot less than 0.96 for each fiscal year ending December 31 occurring during the period of implementation, to be reported each yearin respect of such year and the following (forecast), as well as the previous year (actual). | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section V, Article 2 | Description :Ratio of current assets to current liabilities of not less than0.57 for each fiscal year ending December 31 occurring during the period of implementation, to be reported each year in respect ofsuch year and the following (forecast), as well as the previous year (actual). | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section V, Article 2 | Description :Ratio of current assets to current liabilities of not less than0.57 for fiscal year ending December 31, 2011; 0.57 for 2012; 0.59 for 2013 and 0.57 for 2014 and each fiscal year thereafteroccurring during the period of implementation, to be reported each year in respect of such year and the following (forecast), aswell as the previous year (actual). | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 | No later than the date of execution of the amendment to the loan agreement, the Borrower shallprovide the Bank with evidence demonstrating that the Contractor responsible for the construction of section 1 of the TWWtransmission pipeline has developed and is ensuring the application of a Code of Conduct that has been previously approved by theImplementing Agency

title.narrative: Grievances registered related to delivery of project benefits addressed (%)
Percentage of TWW (not reused) from Northern Tunis WWTP discharged at the submarine outfall
Average annual volume of TWW made available to farmers, developers or municipalities in the vicinity of the Project
Average annual concentration of suspended solids in TWW at the entry point of the transfer system
Average annual concentration of suspended solids in TWW made available at the Sidi Amor reuse pilot
Average annual concentration of suspended solids in TWW made available at the El Hissiene basin
Average annual count of fecal coliforms in seawater samples in the surrounding of the outfall
Average annual count of fecal coliforms in seawater samples at Raoued beach
Percentage of seawater samples at Raoued Beach complying with imperative norms in total coliforms and fecal coliforms (respectively10,000 TC/100ml and 2,000 FC/100ml).
Number of WWTPs and pumping stations in the Northern Tunis system benefiting from equipment rehabilitation and maintenance
